<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="884" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d884">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12970.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 24, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your August 23, 9 p.m. No. 5. It has given me pleasure to bring General
                            Carranza’s message to the attention of the President.</p>
                        <p>This Government desires to express the sincere hope that General Carranza
                            and the people of Mexico will from now on bend every energy to avoid
                            internecine strife, in order that the industrial and economic conditions
                            in Mexico may become normal and that a lasting reign of peace,
                            prosperity and progress may follow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>